      spec: |
        # README.md | markdown | 
        D[59]:
          h1:LiteLLM_Proxy_Client | A Python client library for interacting with the L | 27w
          h2:Installation | ```bash pip install litellm ``` | 5w
          h2:Quick_Start | ```python from litellm.proxy.client import Client | 5w
          h1:Initialize_the_client | client = Client( base_url="http://localhost:4000", | 18w
          h1:Make_a_chat_completion_request | response = client.chat.completions.create( model=" | 16w
          h2:Features | The client is organized into several resource clie | 37w
          h2:Chat_Completions | Make chat completion requests to your LiteLLM prox | 9w
          h1:Basic_chat_completion | response = client.chat.completions.create( model=" | 23w
          h1:Stream_responses | for chunk in client.chat.completions.create( model | 19w
          h2:Model_Management | Manage available models on your proxy:  ```python | 7w
          h1:List_available_models | models = client.models.list() | 3w
          h1:Add_a_new_model | client.models.add(     model_name="gpt-4",     lit | 9w
          h1:Delete_a_model | client.models.delete(model_name="gpt-4") ``` | 2w
          h2:API_Key_Management | Manage virtual API keys:  ```python | 5w
          h1:Generate_a_new_API_key | key = client.keys.generate(     models=["gpt-4", " | 11w
          h1:List_all_keys | keys = client.keys.list(     page=1,     size=10,  | 7w
          h1:Delete_keys | client.keys.delete(     keys=["sk-key1", "sk-key2" | 7w
          h2:Credential_Management | Manage model credentials:  ```python | 4w
          h1:Create_new_credentials | client.credentials.create(     credential_name="az | 11w
          h1:List_all_credentials | credentials = client.credentials.list() | 3w
          h1:Get_a_specific_credential | credential = client.credentials.get(credential_nam | 3w
          h1:Delete_credentials | client.credentials.delete(credential_name="azure1" | 2w
          h2:Model_Groups | Manage model groups for load balancing and fallbac | 9w
          h1:Create_a_model_group | client.model_groups.create(     name="gpt4-group", | 15w
          h1:List_model_groups | groups = client.model_groups.list() | 3w
          h1:Delete_a_model_group | client.model_groups.delete(name="gpt4-group") ``` | 2w
          h2:Users_Management | Manage users on your proxy:  ```python from litell | 14w
          h1:List_users | user_list = users.list_users() | 3w
          h1:Get_user_info | user_info = users.get_user(user_id="u1") | 3w
          h1:Create_a_new_user | created = users.create_user({     "user_email": "a | 14w
          h1:Delete_users | users.delete_user(["u1", "u2"]) ``` | 3w
          h2:Low-Level_HTTP_Client | The client provides access to a low-level HTTP cli | 39w
          h1:Access_the_HTTP_client | client = Client(     base_url="http://localhost:40 | 6w
          h1:Make_a_custom_request | response = client.http.request( method="POST", uri | 19w
          h1:The_response_is_automatically_ | print(response) ``` | 2w
          h3:HTTP_Client_Features | - Automatic URL handling (handles trailing/leading | 39w
          h3:HTTP_Client_`request`_method_p | - `method`: HTTP method (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, e | 56w
          h2:Error_Handling | The client provides clear error handling with cust | 39w
          h2:Advanced_Usage
          h3:Request_Customization | All methods support returning the raw request obje | 13w
          h1:Get_the_prepared_request_witho | request = client.models.list(return_request=True)  | 15w
          h3:Pagination | Methods that return lists support pagination:  ``` | 7w
          h1:Get_the_first_page_of_keys | page1 = client.keys.list(page=1, size=10) | 4w
